his passport behind.</i>

10
00:00:31,633 --> 00:00:32,933
<i>That guy has a
criminal record!</i>

11
00:00:33,067 --> 00:00:33,900
<i> I'll follow them.</i>

12
00:00:34,067 --> 00:00:35,867
<i> Gina, where is Betsy?</i>

13
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:37,267
<i> I haven't talked to her yet.</i>

14
00:00:37,400 --> 00:00:40,400
<i>She checked in here with
the foreigner she dated earlier.</i>

15
00:00:40,533 --> 00:00:41,567
<i> If we do it,</i>

16
00:00:41,700 --> 00:00:44,300
<i>do you promise
to bring me to America?</i>

17
00:00:44,433 --> 00:00:45,700
<i>Oh, yes. I'll marry you,
bring you to America,</i>

18
00:00:45,833 --> 00:00:48,467
<i>and do whatever you want to do.</i>

19
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:51,100
<i>Ma'am, I understand you,
but we are not really allowed</i>

20
00:00:51,233 --> 00:00:53,333
<i>to give information about our
guest.</i>

21
00:00:53,467 --> 00:00:55,967
<i>Ms. Jackie, Mr. Coomer
left his credit card.</i>

22
00:00:56,100 --> 00:00:57,900
<i> Kindly bring it to room 405.</i>

23
00:00:58,033 --> 00:00:59,267
<i> Thank you.</i>

24
00:01:05,667 --> 00:01:07,400
Maybe you should
take a shower first.

25
00:01:07,567 --> 00:01:08,300
Oh, no, no, no.

26
00:01:08,433 --> 00:01:09,533
I'm not taking a shower.

27
00:01:09,667 --> 00:01:12,200
I want you right now,
right here.

28
00:01:12,333 --> 00:01:13,133
We can do it later!

29
00:01:13,267 --> 00:01:15,433
- You shower first!
- No!

30
00:01:15,567 --> 00:01:17,200
- Later!
- No!

31
00:01:17,333 --> 00:01:18,100
No!

32
00:01:53,867 --> 00:01:54,967
- Betsy?
- Betsy!

33
00:01:55,100 --> 00:01:56,033
No!

34
00:01:58,900 --> 00:02:00,800
Oh my god!

35
00:02:00,933 --> 00:02:01,600
Betsy!

36
00:02:01,733 --> 00:02:02,500
Betsy!

37
00:02:02,633 --> 00:02:03,967
Betsy, open the door!

38
