85
00:04:03,900 --> 00:04:05,700
What you're saying is not true.

86
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:09,100
Betsy can't do that to me.

87
00:04:11,300 --> 00:04:13,600
She knows that I won't agree
with her wish for me

88
00:04:13,733 --> 00:04:15,567
to marry you.

89
00:04:15,700 --> 00:04:21,033
So, she will just make a way
to make your dream come true.

90
00:04:25,467 --> 00:04:26,600
Gerald, I'm really sorry.

91
00:04:26,733 --> 00:04:28,467
I should have stopped her more.

92
00:04:30,100 --> 00:04:32,367
I should have been
more insistent.

93
00:04:34,433 --> 00:04:35,733
It's my fault.

94
00:04:40,267 --> 00:04:41,367
It's not your fault, Gina.

95
00:04:43,933 --> 00:04:45,600
If I had pushed her more,
Gerald,

96
00:04:45,733 --> 00:04:47,867
things wouldn't have ended up
like this.

97
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:49,367
I'm really sorry.

98
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:53,667
Sorry.

99
00:05:10,967 --> 00:05:12,000
Sorry.

100
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:25,033
Gerald?

101
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:29,133
Gerald, am I still alive?

102
00:05:33,167 --> 00:05:33,967
Gerald...

103
00:05:36,867 --> 00:05:38,767
You probably know what happened.

104
00:05:41,233 --> 00:05:42,400
I'm sorry.

105
00:05:44,467 --> 00:05:46,133
Don't be mad at me.

106
00:05:48,900 --> 00:05:50,600
Why aren't you talking?

107
00:05:53,300 --> 00:05:55,133
Just tell me...

108
00:05:55,267 --> 00:05:56,833
Yes, I'm mad!

109
00:05:58,600 --> 00:06:00,667
You went with another man!

110
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:03,167
Am I worthless to you anymore?

111
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:05,833
That's not the case.

112
00:06:05,967 --> 00:06:07,667
I'm just making a way!

113
00:06:09,933 --> 00:06:13,467
You don't want to
marry Gina, right?

114
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:17,633
So, I found a way because
I'm not as fuzzy as you!

115
00:06:17,767 --> 00:06:20,233
Betsy, are you thinking?

116
00:06:20,367 --> 00:06:23,767
You're going to give
yourself to a stranger!

117
00:06:23,900 --> 00:06:25,333
I'm taking care of you.

118
00:06:25,467 --> 00:06:27,233
But you're the one who's
putting yourself down!

119
00:06:27,367 --> 00:06:28,700
I don't care!

120
00:06:31,033 --> 00:06:34,667
It's just a body
in exchange for our dreams!

121
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:39,033
He'll take me to America
so I can be with you there!

122
00:06:39,167 --> 00:06:40,233
How else will he take you
to America,

123
00:06:40,367 --> 00:06:42,633
if that animal kills you?

124
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:44,433
How will you get there?

125
00:06:51,767 --> 00:06:52,900
Betsy...

126
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:59,600
America can wait.

127
00:06:59,733 --> 00:07:00,867
The important thing is
that you're okay,

128
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:02,000
you're alive.

129
00:07:06,267 --> 00:07:07,133
Yes, I'm alive...

130
00:07:09,733 --> 00:07:10,567
but it's still the same.

131
00:07:10,700 --> 00:07:12,667
It's still back to zero.

132
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:13,667
I'm still a mess.

133
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:15,967
I still live in the slums!

134
00:07:16,133 --> 00:07:18,033
You don't need
to marry that foreigner

135
00:07:18,167 --> 00:07:20,800
just to get out of here.

136
00:07:20,933 --> 00:07:23,767
Just let me continue
with my plan.

137
00:07:23,900 --> 00:07:25,767
Please?

138
00:07:25,900 --> 00:07:28,300
Gerald, that would take so long!

139
00:07:28,433 --> 00:07:30,633
This is the easiest way!

140
00:07:30,767 --> 00:07:33,467
Can you please stop?

141
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:34,967
Look at what happened to you!

142
00:07:35,100 --> 00:07:35,867
You've been hurt and everything,

143
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,467
and you still
don't want to stop!

144
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:39,533
That's just a coincidence,
Gerald!

145
00:07:39,667 --> 00:07:41,433
There are many other
AFAMs out there!

146
00:07:41,567 --> 00:07:43,933
I'll look for a weak
one who will die soon.

147
00:07:44,067 --> 00:07:45,800
I won't let you! Stop it!

148
00:08:13,300 --> 00:08:16,300
Auntie, I feel sad for
Gerald and for Betsy.

149
00:08:18,833 --> 00:08:21,467
Especially for Betsy.

150
00:08:21,633 --> 00:08:23,600
Can you believe she's
willing to do anything

151
00:08:23,733 --> 00:08:27,033
even if it means killing
her just to get what she wants?

152
00:08:29,067 --> 00:08:31,900
Gina, I understand you.

153
00:08:32,033 --> 00:08:34,200
But there's
nothing you can do.

154
00:08:34,333 --> 00:08:35,967
You've helped her already.

155
00:08:36,100 --> 00:08:38,467
Leave Betsy alone.

156
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:40,433
Auntie, I can't do that.

157
00:08:40,567 --> 00:08:43,467
The last time I did that,
she almost got in danger.

158
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:46,533
she almost got raped.

159
00:08:46,667 --> 00:08:48,833
So, what are you going to do?

160
00:08:48,967 --> 00:08:53,667
You can't save her from her
wrong decisions.

161
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:56,633
And you know, Gina,
I don't understand.

162
00:08:56,800 --> 00:09:00,167
Why are you so concerned
about her?

163
00:09:01,767 --> 00:09:03,700
<i> Let me go!</i>

164
00:09:03,833 --> 00:09:05,933
<i>- Be quiet!
- Let me go!</i>

165
00:09:06,067 --> 00:09:07,000
<i> Help!</i>

166
00:09:11,500 --> 00:09:12,833
<i> Betsy!</i>

167
00:09:18,700 --> 00:09:24,067
Auntie, what happened
to Betsy...

168
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:26,600
It almost happened to me
when I was a kid.

169
00:09:28,733 --> 00:09:30,667
I also got in danger.

170
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:33,933
I almost got raped too.

171
00:09:34,067 --> 00:09:37,533
And Betsy was the
one who helped me.

172
00:09:37,667 --> 00:09:40,133
That's why I made
a promise to myself.

173
00:09:40,267 --> 00:09:43,533
When she needs me,
if she needs my help,

174
00:09:43,667 --> 00:09:45,433
I'll do anything
to make it happen.

175
00:09:47,467 --> 00:09:48,733
Oh my God, Gina.

176
00:10:27,733 --> 00:10:28,633
How are you?

177
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:33,067
Well, my body hurts.

178
00:10:35,833 --> 00:10:38,200
Where's that AFAM?

179
00:10:38,333 --> 00:10:41,133
He's an animal.

180
00:10:41,267 --> 00:10:42,767
He's at the police station.

181
00:10:45,633 --> 00:10:47,100
Betsy, I'm sorry.

182
00:10:49,767 --> 00:10:51,967
I should have done
more to protect you.

183
00:10:53,933 --> 00:10:56,000
It shouldn't have come to this.

184
00:10:58,567 --> 00:11:00,233
That's okay.

185
00:11:00,367 --> 00:11:03,033
Thank you too.

186
00:11:03,167 --> 00:11:05,900
But you shouldn't have followed.

187
00:11:06,033 --> 00:11:08,833
I told you not to interfere,
didn't I?

188
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:12,500
Betsy, what if you die?

189
00:11:12,633 --> 00:11:13,933
I won't die.

190
00:11:15,733 --> 00:11:19,800
I might get beaten
but I won't give up.

191
00:11:19,933 --> 00:11:22,200
I can handle it all.

192
00:11:22,333 --> 00:11:24,733
After all, he said he
would take me to America.

193
00:11:24,867 --> 00:11:25,633
Betsy!

194
00:11:29,133 --> 00:11:32,100
Has my desperation
leveled up?

195
00:11:35,533 --> 00:11:40,500
Sorry, that's the way it is.

196
00:11:40,633 --> 00:11:41,967
I can endure everything.

197
00:11:44,900 --> 00:11:48,833
You probably don't know
what that feels like because...

198
00:11:48,967 --> 00:11:54,067
you don't have to sacrifice
your whole life.

199
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:55,533
I hope same goes for everyone,
right?

200
00:11:59,067 --> 00:12:00,267
It's so confusing.

201
00:12:03,133 --> 00:12:05,367
Wait a minute, Partner.

202
00:12:05,500 --> 00:12:09,133
Betsy still wants to find
a white guy husband?

203
00:12:09,267 --> 00:12:11,600
Isn't she affected by
what happened to her?

204
00:12:15,767 --> 00:12:16,900
What now?

205
00:12:17,033 --> 00:12:18,033
Aren't you going to do anything?

206
00:12:20,333 --> 00:12:22,433
I can't just do nothing.

207
00:12:22,567 --> 00:12:25,433
I have to stop her.

208
00:12:25,567 --> 00:12:27,733
Partner, to be honest,

209
00:12:27,867 --> 00:12:31,033
your process of moving to the US
would be faster

210
00:12:31,167 --> 00:12:34,067
if she marries a US citizen.

211
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:37,600
But if she gets unlucky again.

212
00:12:37,733 --> 00:12:41,667
You might never see
her alive again.

213
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:46,200
I thought of another way to stop
her from doing what she wants.

214
00:12:46,333 --> 00:12:47,333
What way?

215
00:12:49,567 --> 00:12:50,833
I'll stay here with you.

216
00:12:51,467 --> 00:12:53,767
I won't leave you,
I'll be with you.

217
00:12:53,900 --> 00:12:56,367
And if it's necessary,
I'll pay the hospital bill.

218
00:12:56,500 --> 00:12:58,000
No need, Gina. It's okay.

219
00:13:01,533 --> 00:13:05,200
Go back to your happy life
in America.

220
00:13:05,333 --> 00:13:08,000
I'm going back to my
miserable life here.

221
00:13:10,900 --> 00:13:12,167
I don't need your money either

222
00:13:12,300 --> 00:13:17,133
because it won't do anything
to the real problem.

223
00:13:17,267 --> 00:13:21,300
Betsy, I really want
to help you.

224
00:13:22,667 --> 00:13:26,267
Gina, I asked you for help,
didn't I?

225
00:13:28,367 --> 00:13:29,367
But you refused.

226
00:13:31,433 --> 00:13:35,300
You know what Gerald and I
need to get out of here.

227
00:13:57,033 --> 00:13:57,833
Betsy?

228
00:14:08,700 --> 00:14:11,100
You put the foreigner
in jail.

229
00:14:11,233 --> 00:14:12,867
What now?

230
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:14,233
How can you get to America?

231
00:14:14,367 --> 00:14:16,033
He's already in jail!

232
00:14:16,167 --> 00:14:16,933
You idiot!

233
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:22,200
Is that what you're
still thinking?

234
00:14:22,333 --> 00:14:25,400
Didn't you see I got hurt!

235
00:14:25,533 --> 00:14:26,867
What are you? Blind?

236
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:28,567
Or do you just not care?

237
00:14:28,733 --> 00:14:29,833
There you go again.

238
00:14:29,967 --> 00:14:30,867
That's what you're good at!

239
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:32,067
Answer me more!

240
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:34,633
That's why you're getting hurt!

241
00:14:34,767 --> 00:14:36,400
Thank goodness your face
isn't broken,

242
00:14:36,533 --> 00:14:37,467
because if that was broken,

243
00:14:39,967 --> 00:14:41,100
no white guy would like you
anymore.

244
00:14:43,333 --> 00:14:47,300
There's nothing I won't do
to get out of this hellish life.

245
00:14:47,433 --> 00:14:49,067
Even if I have to use Gerald!

246
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:51,200
Really?

247
00:14:51,333 --> 00:14:52,333
You're a pest!

248
00:15:12,567 --> 00:15:15,200
Betsy, eat up.

249
00:15:15,333 --> 00:15:16,467
Just leave me alone.

250
00:15:19,233 --> 00:15:20,367
Go ahead.

251
00:15:20,500 --> 00:15:22,100
Just leave me alone!

252
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:26,367
Nothing will happen
to my life, Gerald.

253
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:32,333
You don't want me to find AFAM,

254
00:15:32,467 --> 00:15:34,167
Gina doesn't want
to marry you either.

255
00:15:36,533 --> 00:15:38,733
Gerald, what will
happen to my life?

256
00:15:43,100 --> 00:15:45,700
You can't do anything to my
life!

257
00:15:45,833 --> 00:15:48,633
If you don't act, Gerald!

258
00:15:48,767 --> 00:15:50,800
What else will happen
to my life?

259
00:15:50,933 --> 00:15:54,233
If Gina won't marry you,
I just want to die!

260
00:15:54,367 --> 00:15:56,367
I just want to die!

261
00:15:56,500 --> 00:15:57,667
Let me die!

262
00:15:57,800 --> 00:15:58,400
I don't want to live anymore!

263
